<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="W" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Weave" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Weave</orth> (impf. <emph>weaved:</emph> Per. <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.0." default="NO" valid="yes">IV Prol. 21</bibl>; partic. <cit><quote>weaved:</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 4.229" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 229</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.4.88" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 4, 88</bibl>. <cit><quote>woven:</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 266" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 266</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.1.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 1, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.121" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 121</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.1.80" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 1, 80</bibl>), to form by texture; absol. (== to practise weaving): <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 2, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.6.194" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 6, 194</bibl>. trans.: <bibl n="shak. ven 266" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 266</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.1.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 1, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.121" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 121</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 2.4.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 4, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.340" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 340</bibl>. Per. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.0." default="NO" valid="yes">IV Prol. 21</bibl>. Metaphorically: <cit><quote>must I ravel out my --d up folly,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 4.229" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 229</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>ill --d ambition,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.4.88" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 4, 88</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>all were woven so strangely in one piece,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 4.1.80" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 1, 80</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>this --s itself perforce into my business,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 2.1.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 1, 17</bibl></cit>. cf. <emph>Unweave.</emph>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>